<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 8:15PM CDT  by NWS Lake Charles</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Jefferson, southeastern Hardin, northwestern Orange and southern
Jasper Counties through 900 PM CDT...
At 814 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Weiss Bluff, or near Lumberton, moving west at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Beaumont, Lumberton, Silsbee, Kountze, Sour Lake, Bevil Oaks, Pine
Forest, Lakeview and Weiss Bluff.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
